      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM DESIRABLE (9) showed pleasing improvement last time out when beaten only 2.8m from this barrier, her third placing from her last four outings. Draws for a trail and could break through. BERTIE JONES NZ (1) only beat one home when resuming at Penrith but was held up. Will be fitter for that and looks to have found a suitable assignment so is worth another chance aided by the ace draw. MAMMALS GIRL (10) has been racing at Menangle of late and was solid when beaten 6.7 metres last start. Draws on the back row but owns a decent record at this circuit and distance. Has the talent to take this out. SHAZADELE (8) draws wide so may need some luck but looks close to a win after placing in her last three outings here.",
